---
// Article 2.1: Labour Department (JTK)
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import AudienceTabs from '../../../components/AudienceTabs.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/panduan-rakyat/Breadcrumb';

const articleData = {
  sectionNumber: '02',
  sectionTitle: 'Work and Employment',
  sectionIcon: '💼',
  articleTitle: 'Labour Department (JTK)',
  articleDescription: 'Understanding your labour rights and JTK services',
  colorRgb: '37, 99, 235',
  lastUpdated: 'March 2026',
};

const simpleContent = `
  <h2 id="what-is-jtk">What is JTK?</h2>
  <p>JTK (Jabatan Tenaga Kerja) is the Labour Department of Malaysia. They protect workers' rights and make sure employers follow the law.</p>
  
  <h2 id="when-to-contact">When to contact JTK:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>💰 Your employer doesn't pay your salary</li>
    <li>📋 You were fired without good reason</li>
    <li>⏰ You work too many hours without overtime pay</li>
    <li>🏖️ You didn't get your annual leave or public holidays</li>
    <li>👶 You didn't get maternity leave</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="how-to-report">How to make a complaint:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Call JTK Hotline:</strong> 1-800-88-6600 (free)</li>
    <li><strong>Visit JTK office:</strong> Go to the nearest JTK office in your state</li>
    <li><strong>Bring documents:</strong> Employment contract, payslips, IC</li>
    <li><strong>Fill complaint form:</strong> JTK officer will help you</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="important-numbers">Important numbers:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>JTK Hotline:</strong> 1-800-88-6600</li>
    <li><strong>JTK Headquarters:</strong> 03-8885 7000</li>
    <li><strong>Website:</strong> jtk.gov.my</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="your-rights">Your basic rights:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Get paid on time</li>
    <li>Maximum 8 hours work per day</li>
    <li>Overtime pay for extra work</li>
    <li>Annual leave and public holidays</li>
    <li>Safe workplace</li>
  </ul>
`;

const detailedContent = `
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>The Jabatan Tenaga Kerja (JTK) or Labour Department is the government agency responsible for enforcing labour laws in Malaysia. Operating under the Ministry of Human Resources, JTK ensures that both employers and employees comply with the Employment Act 1955 and other labour legislation.</p>

  <h2 id="services">Services Provided by JTK</h2>
  <h3>1. Employment Complaints</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Unpaid salary and wages</li>
    <li>Unlawful termination</li>
    <li>Overtime disputes</li>
    <li>Leave entitlement issues</li>
    <li>Retirement benefit disputes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2. Employment Act Enforcement</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Working hours compliance (max 8 hours/day, 48 hours/week)</li>
    <li>Rest day and public holiday entitlements</li>
    <li>Annual leave and sick leave provisions</li>
    <li>Maternity protection</li>
    <li>Minimum wage compliance</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3. Trade Union Affairs</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Trade union registration</li>
    <li>Collective agreement registration</li>
    <li>Industrial relations advice</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4. Foreign Worker Management</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Foreign worker employment pass endorsement</li>
    <li>Employer compliance monitoring</li>
    <li>Foreign worker rights protection</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="how-to-complain">How to Make an Employment Complaint</h2>
  <h3>Step 1: Gather Documents</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Employment contract or offer letter</li>
    <li>Recent payslips (last 3-6 months)</li>
    <li>MyKad or passport copy</li>
    <li>Attendance records (if available)</li>
    <li>Any relevant correspondence (letters, messages, emails)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Step 2: Visit JTK Office</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Go to the JTK office in the state where you work</li>
    <li>Bring all original documents and copies</li>
    <li>Arrive early (offices open 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM, Monday-Friday)</li>
    <li>Take a queue number at the counter</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Step 3: File Complaint Form (Form JTK 1)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>JTK officer will interview you</li>
    <li>Fill out Form JTK 1 (Complaint Form)</li>
    <li>Provide details of employer and complaint</li>
    <li>Submit supporting documents</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Step 4: JTK Investigation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>JTK will summon your employer for inquiry</li>
    <li>Both parties present evidence</li>
    <li>JTK officer makes a decision (Section 69 inquiry)</li>
    <li>If employer loses, JTK issues court order for payment</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Step 5: Enforcement</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>If employer refuses to pay, JTK can take them to court</li>
    <li>Court can order employer to pay owed wages plus penalties</li>
    <li>Employer may face fines or imprisonment for non-compliance</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="time-limits">Time Limits for Complaints</h2>
  <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-border my-4">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-muted">
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">Complaint Type</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">Time Limit</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Unpaid wages</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Within 12 months of wage due date</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Unlawful termination</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Within 60 days of termination</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Overtime disputes</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Within 12 months of OT worked</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Leave entitlement</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Within 12 months</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="coverage">Who is Covered by Employment Act?</h2>
  <h3>Covered:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>✅ All employees earning ≤ RM4,000/month</li>
    <li>✅ Manual workers regardless of salary</li>
    <li>✅ Domestic servants</li>
    <li>✅ Apprentices (registered under Act)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Not Covered:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>❌ Managers and executives earning > RM4,000</li>
    <li>❌ Seafarers (covered by Merchant Shipping Ordinance)</li>
    <li>❌ Domestic workers (some provisions apply)</li>
    <li>❌ Public officers (covered by General Orders)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="important-numbers">JTK Office Locations & Contacts</h2>
  <h3>National Hotline:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>1-800-88-6600</strong> (toll-free)</li>
    <li><strong>03-8885 7000</strong> (HQ)</li>
    <li><strong>Website:</strong> jtk.gov.my</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>State Offices:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Kuala Lumpur:</strong> 03-2693 3599</li>
    <li><strong>Selangor:</strong> 03-5511 4466</li>
    <li><strong>Johor:</strong> 07-224 3533</li>
    <li><strong>Penang:</strong> 04-228 2004</li>
    <li><strong>Sabah:</strong> 088-246 033</li>
    <li><strong>Sarawak:</strong> 082-246 221</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="tips">Tips for Successful Complaints</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>✅ Keep copies of all employment documents</li>
    <li>✅ Record your working hours daily</li>
    <li>✅ Save payslips and bank statements</li>
    <li>✅ Report issues early (within time limits)</li>
    <li>✅ Try to resolve with employer first (if safe)</li>
    <li>✅ Bring a witness if possible</li>
    <li>✅ Be honest and accurate in your complaint</li>
  </ul>
`;

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Is JTK service free?",
    answer: "Yes, all JTK services are completely free. You don't need to pay any fees to file a complaint or seek advice."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does JTK take to resolve a complaint?",
    answer: "Simple cases may be resolved within 2-4 weeks. Complex cases can take 2-6 months depending on evidence and employer cooperation."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I file a complaint if I'm a foreign worker?",
    answer: "Yes! Foreign workers have the same rights as Malaysian workers under the Employment Act. JTK protects all workers regardless of nationality."
  },
  {
    question: "What if my employer threatens me for complaining?",
    answer: "This is illegal victimization. Report threats to JTK immediately. Employers who victimize workers face additional penalties."
  },
  {
    question: "Do I need a lawyer to file a JTK complaint?",
    answer: "No, JTK handles complaints directly without requiring lawyers. However, you can consult a lawyer if you wish."
  }
];

const headings = [
  { id: 'overview', title: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'services', title: 'Services Provided', level: 2 },
  { id: 'how-to-complain', title: 'How to Make a Complaint', level: 2 },
  { id: 'time-limits', title: 'Time Limits', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage', title: 'Who is Covered?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'tips', title: 'Tips for Success', level: 2 },
];
---

<Layout title={`${articleData.articleTitle} | People's Guide | EduLaluan`}>
  <Header />

  <main class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section 
      class="relative overflow-hidden py-section-lg border-b"
      style={{
        '--section-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
        'border-bottom-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`
      }}
    >
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl">
          <!-- Breadcrumb -->
          <Breadcrumb items={[
            { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
            { label: "People's Guide", href: '/panduan-rakyat' },
            { label: `Section ${articleData.sectionNumber}`, href: `/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}` },
            { label: articleData.articleTitle }
          ]} />

          <!-- Back Button -->
          <a
            href={`/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}`}
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-primary transition-colors mb-6"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
            </svg>
            Back to Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}
          </a>

          <!-- Article Title -->
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mt-6">
            <div 
              class="flex h-16 w-16 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-3xl"
              style={{ 
                'backgroundColor': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
                'color': 'white'
              }}
            >
              {articleData.sectionIcon}
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary mb-1 tracking-wide uppercase">
                Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}: {articleData.sectionTitle}
              </p>
              <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-foreground">
                {articleData.articleTitle}
              </h1>
              <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mt-3">
                {articleData.articleDescription}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-surface">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="flex gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <!-- Main Content -->
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <!-- Audience Tabs (Simple/Detailed) -->
            <AudienceTabs>
              <Fragment slot="simple" set:html={simpleContent} />
              <Fragment slot="detailed" set:html={detailedContent} />
            </AudienceTabs>

            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="mt-12">
              <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6">
                Frequently Asked Questions
              </h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                {faqs.map((faq) => (
                  <details
                    class="group rounded-xl border bg-surface-elevated transition-all"
                  >
                    <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 font-semibold text-foreground list-none">
                      {faq.question}
                      <svg
                        class="h-5 w-5 text-muted-foreground transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                      >
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                      </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-muted-foreground">
                      {faq.answer}
                    </div>
                  </details>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Last Updated -->
            <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-border">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                <strong>Last updated:</strong> {articleData.lastUpdated}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Table of Contents (Sidebar) -->
          <aside class="sticky top-24 hidden lg:block w-64 shrink-0">
            <nav class="space-y-1" aria-label="Table of contents">
              <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">
                On This Page
              </h3>
              {headings.map((heading) => (
                <a
                  href={`#${heading.id}`}
                  class="block py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
                  style={{ paddingLeft: `${(heading.level - 2) * 12 + 12}px` }}
                >
                  {heading.title}
                </a>
              ))}
            </nav>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation Footer -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-background">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-surface-elevated p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-muted-foreground">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p class="text-sm">
                <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only. Always verify with official sources for the most current information.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Section padding utilities */
  :root {
    --section-padding-lg: clamp(3rem, 5vw + 1rem, 5rem);
    --section-padding-md: clamp(2rem, 3vw + 1rem, 3rem);
  }

  .py-section-lg {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-lg);
  }

  .py-section-md {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-md);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-md);
  }

  /* Article Typography */
  .prose-panduan {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan ul,
  .prose-panduan ol {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan a {
    color: var(--primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .prose-panduan a:hover {
    color: var(--primary-dark);
  }

  .prose-panduan strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .prose-panduan th {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose-panduan td {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose-panduan .bg-muted {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
</style>
